<dl id="n54141c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54141c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54141c"> 141(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> wound footprint <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54141c"><li>FW 278.25 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/lexlf.htm#n54141c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lf/l39lf.htm#n54141c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54141c">MS BL 47478-339</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:318 <a name="lad13" href="../../ff/fdra/lda.htm#lfd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lf/lfd4.htm#n54141c">Draft: II.2&sect;7.4</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Dans le cas pr&eacute;sent, il est impossible aux Papous de se procurer directement l&apos;empreinte qui les mettrait en possession du raroai de leurs ennemis. Ils ont recours &agrave; un proc&eacute;d&eacute; ing&eacute;nieux. Le raroai dont s&apos;impr&egrave;gne l&apos;empreinte dont ils veulent s&apos;emparer passera a une feuille enterr&eacute;e expr&egrave;s &agrave; l&apos;endroit o&ugrave; les ennemis posent le pied, et cette feuille fera ensuite l&apos;office de l&apos;empreinte. C&apos;est pour ainsi dire un symbole de symbole, un symbole au second degr&eacute;. L&apos;action qu&apos;il va permettre d&apos;exercer n&apos;en sera pas moins efficace. La vari&eacute;t&eacute; m&ecirc;me des formes que rev&ecirc;t cette action symbolique fait ressortir l&apos;id&eacute;e dont elles proc&egrave;dent toutes: pour paralyser un ennemi ou un animal dans sa marche, il suffit <mark>de blesser l&apos;empreinte de son pied</mark>. <br><font color="green">[In the present case, it is impossible for the Papuans to obtain directly the imprint which would put them in possession of the raroai of their enemies. They use an ingenious process. The raroai with which they imprint the imprint which they want to take will pass to a leaf buried expressly at the place where the enemies set foot, and this leaf will then make the office of the imprint. It&apos;s like a symbol symbol, a symbol in the second degree. The action that it will allow to exercise will not be less effective. The very variety of forms that this symbolic action takes brings out the idea from which they all proceed: to paralyze an enemy or an animal in its march, it suffices to injure the imprint of its foot.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 232</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
